===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{lb|en|uncountable}} The [[technology]] that allows for the [[transmission]] of sound or other signals by [[modulation]] of [[electromagnetic wave]]s.
# {{lb|en|countable}} A device that can capture (receive) the signal sent over radio waves and render the modulated signal as [[sound]].
# {{lb|en|countable}} On-board entertainment system in a car, usually including a radio receiver as well as the capability to play audio from recorded media.
#* {{quote-web|en|author=Jonathan Amos|title=Elon Musk's huge Falcon Heavy rocket set for launch|work=BBC News|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-42950957|location=London, United Kingdom|publisher=BBC|date=2018-02-06|accessdate=2018-02-07|passage=David Bowie's classic hit Space Oddity will be looping on the '''radio''' as the car is hurled into an elliptical orbit that stretches out to Mars' orbit around the Sun.}}
# {{lb|en|countable}} A device that can transmit radio signals.
# {{lb|en|Internet|uncountable}} The continuous [[broadcast]]ing of [[sound]] via the [[Internet]] in the style of traditional radio.

